readme:
Service Usage

This service is used by the consumer to create a referral for a specific applicant in a visa application.
A referral is a request from one DIAC work area to another to undertake some activity, for a specific purpose related to the processing of an application.

Service Behaviour

The consumer of this service will provide:
Visa Application ID
Party ID of the specific applicant for whom the referral is being created
The type of referral
The status of the referral
The method of transfer
The reason for the referral
Reference ID of the supporting document
Notes applicable for an officer processing the referral
Reference ID of the scanned/digitised documents
This service will record the referral details, generate its unique identifier (referral request ID) and link it to the given visa application ID.
A consumer of this service receives either:
Unique Identifier of the referral and its status

Or
An Enterprise Error detailing why create was unsuccessful.

Service Variants

This service has no service variants.

Service Dependencies

This service relies on the consumer already having a unique identifier of a Visa Application as a Visa Application Id.

Service Composition

There is no Composition call.

Service Flow

The following service flow describes a successful execution path.

  1. The Consumer invokes the service on ESB.
  2. Consumer provides ICSE ClientId to call ICSE otherwise Service throw Exception.
  3. ESB validate request data.
  4. ESB invokes service provider ICSE for Create Visa Application Referral.
  5. ICSE returns the Referral Request Id and sequence number of the newly created Visa Application referral to ESB.
  6. ESB transforms ICSE response into CreateVisaApplicationReferralResponse.
  7. ESB returns CreateVisaApplicationReferralResponse to Consumer.

1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider (ICSE) raises an error.

  1. The Consumer invokes the service on ESB.
  2. ESB validate request data.
  3. Consumer provides ICSE ClientId to call ICSE otherwise Service throw Exception.
  4. ESB invokes service provider ICSE for Create Visa Application Referral.
  5. ICSE returns response to ESB.
  6. ESB detects that ICSE has returned an error.
  7. ESB transforms ICSE error into Enterprise Error Message.
  8. ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload to Consumer.

1.1.2 Alternate Flow 3
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when ESB data validation fails.

  1. The Consumer invokes the service on ESB.
  2. ESB validate request data.
  3. ESB found some data not as expected or not match.
  4. ESB transforms the validation error into Enterprise Error Message.
  5. ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload to Consumer.
